Oct 15 2009 	Excellent value for money in central San Fran	Despite dodgy reviews here, our tight budget led us to book 3 nights at the Grant Plaza in mid-September.As expected for $60 a night, the room was small, but there was plenty of storage for our bags (we were on a 2-week road trip, so quite a lot of stuff). The bed was comfy and the room and bathroom were spotlessly clean. There was no view from our room - we looked onto a central courtyard, but this meant it was pretty quiet, which suited us. We literally only slept and washed in the room and spent all day out and about.Maid service was brilliant - the room was obviously hoovered every day and sheets and towels changed.The best bit has to be the location - so central to everything. We walked a lot around the city, and the hotel was always a reasonable distance from wherever we ended up.Highly recommend this for travellers on a budget, or, like us, if you know the only time you'll be spending in your room really will be sleeping.Also recommend busting the budget on french toast at Cafe de la Presse down one block towards Unions Square. Delish!	
