Jul 29 2009 	Convient	We stayed here for 1 night because the hotel we were at in the Valley wouldn't extend our good price for one more night. We didn't expect much since we had read all the reviews. Still we were surprised. It's a basic no frills hotel, but it was very nicely located 1 block inside China town. It was clean and comfortable. Our room was on the 5th floor Grant Street side, so it was pretty noisy with the windows open until about 9pm. Most of the shops had closed by then and foot traffic was sparse. The bathroom was outdated and the floor was chipped and a little run down, but the shower worked well. They included a shower soap dispenser and 3 little hotel soaps. No shampoo or conditioner. We had our own, so it didn't matter. The bathroom even had a hair dryer.It was so easy to walk to all the main attractions from there, or hop on the BART to get outside the inner city. Eating establishments were everywhere. We had 3 Starbucks within a 3 block walk. A nice sandwich shop called the 3 Sisters was 2 blocks away serving breakfast and lunch sandwiches like Corn Beef Hash or Pesto Salmon at an average price of $8. Way too many choices to name here. Several breakfast places for sit down service too.It's up a steep hill which can be intimidating with luggage, but you can park right outside the hotel, unload, check in and get your parking pass. Parking is about 3 blocks away and reasonable at $22.80 for 24 hours. ( It costs $5.80 pp for transport from SFO BART one way, if you'd rather not deal with the car aspect.)The girl in the morning is very friendly and helpful. The older gentleman later in the day was not so much. Neither was the younger man being trained. I think it's because they didn't speak much English. Internet is available for a price. You can stow your luggage in a good size locker for 50 cents if you get there too early.A sign in the window advertises rooms starting at $55 a night. Our twin room was $69 a night . The only way up was to use an elevator which was surprisingly quick. They had a locked door at the bottom of the stairs on the first floor that only let you go down. We didn't go back and forth to the room that much to care.We would definitely stay here again.	
Jun 26 2009	excellent location and pleasant staff	When you are sight-seeing the room is a low priority. Rented two rooms for 3 days and was very satisfied. The location was excellent...close to sights, food and transportation. Sure the rooms are small but they are clean and pleasant enough when used primarily for sleeping. Staff was friendly and helpfull. Parking was available and only 3 blocks away. If you are going to spend many hours in your room this may not be the place for you, but if as we were, you are seeing the city for 14 hours a day the Grant Plaza is a great place to stay and you can use your money for other things.	
