Apr 19 2009 	Excellent location on a budget	Location is excellent, right at the southern entrance of Chinatown. Public transport is only a block or 2 away and you can get to pretty much any of the tourist attractions on offer. It's about 5 blocks to the nearest BART station that can take you to/from the airport for about $5.50 one way. Most tour companies do pickup from this hotel.The room is a bit dirty, smelly and very small. I got given a room on the upper level with view to the street and it is fairly noisy from the traffic at night. There's no Air Conditioning in the room so I can't just shut the window to keep noise out. The shower is very tiny. I can barely find room to fit myself in it. The windows are full height without bars, even on upper level, so it's not for someone with kids as you can easily fall off the building through the open window. The staff are quite friendly and helpful. There's internet access in the lobby if required for a fee. Otherwise, there's not much common facilities on offer. Despite the shortfalls, I would stay here again because of the value and location.	
