d does is not even concerned with upgrading their rickety fun-house elevator which made us fear for our lives, so much so that we opted for 5 flights of stairs over the elevator of death. The funniest thing about the room was the phone book. The hotel section of the phone book had been ripped out, probably by another persong who was fed up by the terrible service that they took that page to go find another hotel. I'm serious, do not stay there.I'm not a hotel snob; I've stayed at Motel 6's and Econo Lodges and been totally content. All I ask for is a little room so I can at least fit between the dresser and the bed. The dresser and bed in our room were literally 5 inches apart, and they expected us to happily walk through it one leg at a time to get to the other side of the room and the bathroom. Speaking of bathrooms, ours was apalling. I opened the door and got the impression that the shower hadn't been cleaned since the Korean War. There are other hotels in SF that cost the same amount that aren't disgusting. The staff should be ashamed of themselves. Please, for the love of god, do not stay there.	
