Sep 28 2005	Great value	This place is maybe a step or two above a hostel, but for 60 bucks in the heart of San Francisco it's a great deal. It's clean, safe, the rooms have a private bathroom, and it's a 15-minute walk from the Embarcadero. It's especially good to find this kind of a rate on the good side of Union Square (i.e., not in the tenderloin). Yes, it's a block into Chinatown, but it's also two blocks from the Banana Republic flagship store and Union Square. It's true that the lobby smells funky. And there's only a twin bed in a small, beat-up room with an old TV. But you get what you pay for. The earlier reviewer who went here on their honeymoon--are you serious? Like another person said, don't bring your girlfriend here, but it's a great find if you're just looking for a clean, safe place to sleep.	
