Sep 18 2005 	Good value for money great location	I booked a last minute trip to SF and reserved my hotel through the Visitor's Bureau website. Having lived in SF in my grad school days, I wanted something close to transport and central city, but reasonably priced. The Grant Plaza was all of that. I had a 6th floor room, which was tiny, yes, but I only needed a place to sleep and shower, which was fine. The room did not face Chinatown's main street (some say that is the noisier side), there was some city noise (er, that's what to expect in a city, even at the best hotels!) but nothing horrible. Clean room, spotless (tiny) bathroom, great water pressure, tv, comfy bed. Cheerful staff and lots of travellers who knew they had found a bargain. Chinatown, Union Suare and Fisherman's Wharf are all nearby, public transport is close, and there are plenty of great places to eat nearby in Chinatown and Little Italy. As a single woman travelling alone, I felt perfectly safe---something that is very important.	
