Jul 27 2005	Loved the Grant Plaza	My daughter and I spent 5 nights at the Grant Plaza and were both quite pleased with our room, and would definitely return again. Our room was small with 2 twin beds and very clean. The shower stall is small, but the water pressure was great. It sure beat the water pressure at the Hilton in San Mateo. I was concerned that it might be noisy at night because I am a very light sleeper, but never heard our neighbors and while we did hear traffic at night it did not keep us awake. The staff was very friendly and helpful. We asked for and received advice on restaurants, busses, and other tourist info and were quite pleased with all recommendations. I would recommend this hotel to anyone on a budget for its cleanliness, excellent staff and proximity to many attractions. We used public transportation and found the Grant Plaza to be a great location to catch a bus to anywhere we wanted to go. The 6th floor has been recently remodelled (we were on the 5th floor), so they may be in process of a full update for the hotel.	
